additionalInfo.description:
CAI Process not loading in Azure POD
The customer has reported that they imported a connection and a process into their Test ORG using GITHUB. When they are seeing is that the connection has a unique name - con-Snowflake-EDNA-1. There is no other connection with this name in the org. 

Also, when the customer tries to open the process - aip_MerchantPlanQuery, it does not load in the designer and the UI simply hangs.  Please see the attached screenshot.

I had a meeting with the customer and looked at the connection and the process. When I logged on to the customer org on our end using GCS account, the process did not load. So, the issue is consistently reproducible.  

New connections \ process created in this org work fine. So, the issue seems to be specific to the artifacts imported into the org from Git.
